Our prevention measures include the use of:

??A? chlorine detectors and alarms to rapidly alert operators to any problems;
??A? a chlorine scrubber designed to contain and remove a major chlorine release;
??A? process safety information to document the safe process design;
??A? process hazards analyses to evaluate the chemical and process hazards;
??A? operating procedures to ensure that the system is operated safely;
??A? maintenance, inspection and testing to ensure that the system is maintained according to applicable standards and manufacturer's recommendations;
??A? training, hot work permits, contractor safety and employee participation programs to ensure that all employees and contractors working on and around the processes are aware of the hazards, can perform their job duties safely and know the actions to be taken in an emergency;
??A? management of change and pre-startup safety reviews to ensure that changes are documented, analyzed and kept within the design basis;
??A? incident investigation procedure to investigate each incident and "near misses" to determine root causes and make needed safety improvements;
??A? and periodic compliance audits to ensure that our programs are working as they should to protect both employees and the public.

Five-Year Accident History

Within the past five years, the Citico Plant has not had one accident due to a chlorine release that resulted in either injury or property damage. The plant has maintained an excellent safety record throughout its operating history and has never had a major chlorine release with off-site impacts having adverse effects on the public.  

